access_rule.policy:
We ask that you adhere to a strict cancellation policy. Out of respect for our partner restaurants, we ask that you modify any reservations that you will not be able to honor 24 hours before your scheduled reservation. Should no-shows occur, the restaurant reserves the right to remove online access privileges as well as forfeiting any reservation deposit. To modify your reservation, please use the modify link contained within the confirmation email. Please note, canceling your reservation automatically forfeits your reservation and non refundable deposit.
 

DISCLAIMER: We have taken enhanced health and safety measures—for you, our guest and staff. An inherent risk of exposure to COVID-19 exists in any public place where people are present. COVID-19 is an extremely contagious disease that can lead to severe illness and death. According to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, senior citizens and visitors with underlying medical conditions are especially vulnerable. By visiting Negril BK you assume all risks related to exposure to COVID-19 and agree to the all safety measures stated by the CDC and Guidelines of the New York Department of Health. 
 

Our current business hours are as follows: 
Mondays: Closed 

Tuesdays - Sundays: ‪2pm - 9pm for outdoor seating, last seating 8pm.

Tuesdays - Sundays: 2pm-10pm for indoor seating, last seating 8pm. 
 

We appreciate your interest in Negril BK. We are extremely excited to welcome you our guests back into our restaurant.  
 

Due to the limited seating restrictions, we can only accommodate online reservations via our website Negrilbk.com at this time. Our maximum number of guests will be for groups of up to 6 guests maximum for dining. Due to citywide occupancy restrictions, we are unable to accommodate increases in party size at this time. Restaurant reserves the right to reject reservations inconsistent with this policy.
 

Guests are asked to check-in with our hostess upon arrival. Temperature checks will be mandatory to enter the building and guests will be asked to leave their contact information for at least one member of their party for contact tracing.  
 

For indoor seating we require a $20 non-refundable deposit to secure your reservation, this deposit goes towards final payment of your bill. Please note that we hold your reservation for 10 minutes, should you show up late or not show at all, you will forfeit your deposit.  
 
Currently we also offer outdoor service (weather permitting) for groups up to 6 guests maximum for dining. Due to the limited available space, outdoor seating is first come first serve for. Unfortunately, we cannot accommodate reservations at this time for outdoor seating. 
 

We also offer delivery, pick-up and curbside service during our normal business hours. If you have any questions, please don’t hesitate to reach out. 
 

Please feel free to download our Negril BK App. New users who sign up will receive 15% off their entire order.

times.policy:
We ask that you adhere to a strict cancellation policy. Out of respect for our partner restaurants, we ask that you modify any reservations that you will not be able to honor 24 hours before your scheduled reservation. Should no-shows occur, the restaurant reserves the right to remove online access privileges as well as forfeiting any reservation deposit. To modify your reservation, please use the modify link contained within the confirmation email. Please note, canceling your reservation automatically forfeits your reservation and non refundable deposit.
 

DISCLAIMER: We have taken enhanced health and safety measures—for you, our guest and staff. An inherent risk of exposure to COVID-19 exists in any public place where people are present. COVID-19 is an extremely contagious disease that can lead to severe illness and death. According to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, senior citizens and visitors with underlying medical conditions are especially vulnerable. By visiting Negril BK you assume all risks related to exposure to COVID-19 and agree to the all safety measures stated by the CDC and Guidelines of the New York Department of Health. 
 

Our current business hours are as follows: 
Mondays: Closed 

Tuesdays - Sundays: ‪2pm - 9pm for outdoor seating, last seating 8pm.

Tuesdays - Sundays: 2pm-10pm for indoor seating, last seating 8pm. 
 

We appreciate your interest in Negril BK. We are extremely excited to welcome you our guests back into our restaurant.  
 

Due to the limited seating restrictions, we can only accommodate online reservations via our website Negrilbk.com at this time. Our maximum number of guests will be for groups of up to 6 guests maximum for dining. Due to citywide occupancy restrictions, we are unable to accommodate increases in party size at this time. Restaurant reserves the right to reject reservations inconsistent with this policy.
 

Guests are asked to check-in with our hostess upon arrival. Temperature checks will be mandatory to enter the building and guests will be asked to leave their contact information for at least one member of their party for contact tracing.  
 

For indoor seating we require a $20 non-refundable deposit to secure your reservation, this deposit goes towards final payment of your bill. Please note that we hold your reservation for 10 minutes, should you show up late or not show at all, you will forfeit your deposit.  
 
Currently we also offer outdoor service (weather permitting) for groups up to 6 guests maximum for dining. Due to the limited available space, outdoor seating is first come first serve for. Unfortunately, we cannot accommodate reservations at this time for outdoor seating. 
 

We also offer delivery, pick-up and curbside service during our normal business hours. If you have any questions, please don’t hesitate to reach out. 
 

Please feel free to download our Negril BK App. New users who sign up will receive 15% off their entire order.

We ask that you adhere to a strict cancellation policy. Out of respect for our partner restaurants, we ask that you modify any reservations that you will not be able to honor 24 hours before your scheduled reservation. Should no-shows occur, the restaurant reserves the right to remove online access privileges as well as forfeiting any reservation deposit. To modify your reservation, please use the modify link contained within the confirmation email. Please note, canceling your reservation automatically forfeits your reservation and non refundable deposit.
 

DISCLAIMER: We have taken enhanced health and safety measures—for you, our guest and staff. An inherent risk of exposure to COVID-19 exists in any public place where people are present. COVID-19 is an extremely contagious disease that can lead to severe illness and death. According to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, senior citizens and visitors with underlying medical conditions are especially vulnerable. By visiting Negril BK you assume all risks related to exposure to COVID-19 and agree to the all safety measures stated by the CDC and Guidelines of the New York Department of Health. 
 

Our current business hours are as follows: 
Mondays: Closed 

Tuesdays - Sundays: ‪2pm - 9pm for outdoor seating, last seating 8pm.

Tuesdays - Sundays: 2pm-10pm for indoor seating, last seating 8pm. 
 

We appreciate your interest in Negril BK. We are extremely excited to welcome you our guests back into our restaurant.  
 

Due to the limited seating restrictions, we can only accommodate online reservations via our website Negrilbk.com at this time. Our maximum number of guests will be for groups of up to 6 guests maximum for dining. Due to citywide occupancy restrictions, we are unable to accommodate increases in party size at this time. Restaurant reserves the right to reject reservations inconsistent with this policy.
 

Guests are asked to check-in with our hostess upon arrival. Temperature checks will be mandatory to enter the building and guests will be asked to leave their contact information for at least one member of their party for contact tracing.  
 

For indoor seating we require a $20 non-refundable deposit to secure your reservation, this deposit goes towards final payment of your bill. Please note that we hold your reservation for 10 minutes, should you show up late or not show at all, you will forfeit your deposit.  
 
Currently we also offer outdoor service (weather permitting) for groups up to 6 guests maximum for dining. Due to the limited available space, outdoor seating is first come first serve for. Unfortunately, we cannot accommodate reservations at this time for outdoor seating. 
 

We also offer delivery, pick-up and curbside service during our normal business hours. If you have any questions, please don’t hesitate to reach out. 
 

Please feel free to download our Negril BK App. New users who sign up will receive 15% off their entire order.
